ExecDesc.value: RealNetworks RealPlayer MPG Width Integer Underflow Memory Corruption

EngDesc.value: An integer underflow vulnerability exists in RealPlayer's handling of MPEG movies. The vulnerability is caused when the application subtracts one from a user controlled value that is then used as a loop iterator. A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open a specially crafted MPEG file. Successful exploitation can lead to the injection and execution of arbitrary code in the context of the currently logged in user.
